Sir Alex Ferguson has admitted he had to change his everyday habits as he got older to continue managing Manchester United .
Ferguson enjoyed a trophy-laden 26-and-a-half years in the Old Trafford where he won 38 trophies - including 13 Premier League titles and two Champions League successes .
The Scot was appointed as the Red Devils manager in November 1986 at the age of 45 before announcing his retirement at the end of the 2012-13 season aged 71 .